The article discusses the recent accord reached between the United States, Israel, and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) on August 13, 2020. The accord is seen as a courageous step towards a more stable, integrated, and prosperous Middle East. It aims to de-escalate existing conflicts and prevent future conflicts by focusing on pragmatic steps with tangible outcomes. The accord has led to the normalization of ties between Israel and the UAE, suspending Israel's plans to extend its sovereignty. The UAE has abolished its 40-year boycott law, allowing direct trade with Israel. The two countries have initiated discussions on cooperation in various areas, including investment, finance, health, space, aviation, foreign policy, and tourism. The article expresses gratitude for the positive response to the accord from governments worldwide and acknowledges the leadership of President Donald J. Trump in achieving this diplomatic breakthrough. The hope is that this accord will bring about positive changes and lead to security, prosperity, and peace in the region.